Comparing Four Measures of Codon Bias

Full set of genes: 1620 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level across 22 strains

Partial set of genes: 185 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level and identical at the amino acid sequence level across 22 strains

7/18/2022

library(car)
library(lme4)
library(reshape2)

Analysis of Codon Bias on the Full Set of Genes

Define the response variable.

response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1620_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$sqrtPPR <- (dataset$PPR)^(1/2)

Codon Adaptation Index (CAI) with Carbone Reference Set

Menu
Read in Data
explanatory1 <- read.csv('CAI_Carbone_1620_YRC_diff_d.csv')
explanatory1 <- melt(explanatory1, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "CAI")
dataset$CAI <- explanatory1$CAI
Summary Results of Mixed Model
lmm1 <- lmer(sqrtPPR ~ CAI + (1+CAI|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="Nelder_Mead", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
summary(lmm1)
## Linear mixed model fit by maximum likelihood  ['lmerMod']
## Formula: sqrtPPR ~ CAI + (1 + CAI | gene)
##    Data: dataset
## Control: lmerControl(optimizer = "Nelder_Mead", optCtrl = list(maxfun = 1e+05))
## 
##      AIC      BIC   logLik deviance df.resid 
## 114548.2 114599.1 -57268.1 114536.2    35634 
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -11.9442  -0.4473   0.0216   0.4719  11.9891 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name        Variance Std.Dev. Corr
##  gene     (Intercept)  525.644 22.9269      
##           CAI         2127.360 46.1233  0.14
##  Residual                0.929  0.9639      
## Number of obs: 35640, groups:  gene, 1620
## 
## Fixed effects:

## (Intercept)  48.7611     0.7218  67.558
## CAI          17.6296     2.5906   6.805
## 
## Correlation of Fixed Effects:
##     (Intr)
## CAI -0.490
95% Confidence Interval of Mixed Model
confint(lmm1, parm="CAI", level=0.95)
## Computing profile confidence intervals ...
##        2.5 %   97.5 %
## CAI 12.39258 22.98069
Fixed Effects Slope Significance Results
lmm2 <- lmer(sqrtPPR ~ (1+CAI|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
anova(lmm1, lmm2)
## Data: dataset
## Models:
## lmm2: sqrtPPR ~ (1 + CAI | gene)
## lmm1: sqrtPPR ~ CAI + (1 + CAI | gene)
##      npar    AIC    BIC logLik deviance  Chisq Df Pr(>Chisq)    
## lmm2    5 114590 114633 -57290   114580                         
## lmm1    6 114548 114599 -57268   114536 44.135  1  3.064e-11 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm1)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm1), res, col='slateblue', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$CAI, res, col='slateblue', span=0.1, xlab='CAI (Carbone)', ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='slateblue')
qqline(res)
hist(res, main='', xlab='Residuals', ylab='Frequency', col='slateblue')

anova(lmm7, lmm8)
## Data: dataset
## Models:
## lmm8: sqrtPPR ~ (0 + ntAI | gene)
## lmm7: sqrtPPR ~ ntAI + (0 + ntAI | gene)

## lmm8    3 11311 11330 -5652.7    11305                        
## lmm7    4 11306 11331 -5648.8    11298 7.7996  1   0.005226 **

Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm7)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm7), res, col='peru', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$ntAI, res, col='peru', span=0.1, xlab='ntAI', ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='peru')
qqline(res)
hist(res, main='', xlab='Residuals', ylab='Frequency', col='peru')
